snippet.textDisplay: Conor sounds different hes not as cocky as he once was which is a good thing and realizing he made mistakes and didnt take things they way he should or played into things he shouldnt have..conor seems focused once again which is a very good thing but he was hesitant when masvidal was mentioned and he made the comment hes not coming to 170 for masvidal cuz he has nothing to offer but yet again ur coming to 170 for cerrone..ya cerrone has alot of records and hes a good fighter and hes a warrior but hes never held the title and then justin is mentioned and hes all about that he even mentions usman and Colby but was masvidal has nothing to offer c'mon I believe Conor will avoid masvidal ...madvidal is a tremendous striker and his hands are deadly...if conor fights masvidal at 170 that's dangerous for Conor...if he wants the welterweight belt hes gonna have to fight masvidal you would think and if wins the title hes gonna have to fight masvidal...if conor can elevate his game and capture the welterweight title the amount of money McGregor vs masvidal would make would be crazy...but conor First needs wins against suitable tough competition...do I think he beats usman umm no unless his wrestling massively improves or usman plays a dangerous game and wants to strike...if he does yes Conor can beat usman...but I think once usman sees Conor very dangerous stand up game I think Usman takes him down and pounds him out...as for justin well hes much bigger than McGregor and if he gets in a all out war he could get knocked out but I'm still not sold on Conor power 170..I dont think it's as dangerous in this bigger weight class as for masvidal well dude has power..hes a on point striker,very dangerous his stand up game is up there...pick your poison he can land the hands or finish u with knees..ultimately conor has to be back to his old self hungry and determined and just work on his skills...will it be enough to capture the welterweight I dont know..that's a tough task in a stacked division with some very tough fighters...as for khabib being scared I highly doubt it...unless conor can keep the fight standing he has no chance at beating khabib...khabib dropped him with a good shot..I dont believe it was lucky I do believe Conor thinks his striking ability his way better than everybody so ofcourse he wasnt concerned with khabib hands until they landed...khabib mauls McGregor and just breaks him down yet again...khabib has that effect on fighters
